<doc id="340069" wikidata="Q866560" url="?curid=340069" title="Coeranoscincus">
<text>Coeranoscincus is a genus of skinks. They are endemic to Australia and found in eastern Queensland and northeastern New South Wales.

==Species==
There are two species:
*&quot;Coeranoscincus frontalis&quot; – limbless snake-tooth skink
*&quot;Coeranoscincus reticulatus&quot; – three-toed snake-tooth skink

