<doc id="340070" wikidata="Q835693" url="?curid=340070" title="Cophoscincopus">
<text>Cophoscincopus (common name: keeled water skinks) is a genus of skinks, lizards in the family Scincidae. The genus is endemic to West Africa. As suggested by the common name, species in the genus &quot;Cophoscincopus&quot; are semi-aquatic.

==Species==
There are four recognized species in the genus &quot;Cophoscincopus&quot;.
*&quot;Cophoscincopus durus&quot; 
*&quot;Cophoscincopus greeri&quot; 
*&quot;Cophoscincopus senegalensis&quot; 
*&quot;Cophoscincopus simulans&quot; 

&quot;Nota bene&quot;: A binomial authority in parentheses indicates that the species was originally described in a genus other than &quot;Cophoscincopus&quot;.

